{{Infobox person | name = Bilal Lashari | image = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | nationality = Pakistani | other_names = | occupation = Actor, Director, Writer | years_active = 2004–present | known_for = [[Waar]] [[Khuda Kay Liye]] | spouse = | awards = [[#Awards|see below]] | website = | birthname = | religion = }}
'''Bilal Lashari''' is a Pakistani film director, cinematographer, screenwriter and occasional actor.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bilal Lashari dips his hands in films|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/597329/bilal-lashari-dips-his-hands-in-films|accessdate=28 May 2014|newspaper=DAWN.com|date=9 January 2014}}</ref> He made his directorial debut film in ''[[Waar]]'' (2013), which holds the record of being the [[List of highest-grossing Pakistani films|fourth highest-grossing Pakistani film]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Rafay Mahmood|title=It's official, Waar is the highest grossing Pakistani film of all time|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/636060/its-official-waar-is-the-highest-grossing-pakistani-film-of-all-time/|accessdate=28 May 2014|newspaper=The Express Tribune|date=23 November 2013}}</ref> His next project is remake of 1979 film [[Maula Jatt]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Rafay Mahmood|title=Bilal Lashari's next project: A multi-million dollar remake of Maula Jatt|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/645491/bilal-lasharis-next-project-a-multi-million-dollar-remake-of-maula-jatt/|accessdate=28 May 2014|newspaper=The Express Tribune|date=14 December 2013}}</ref> Lashari won awards in four categories at the [[ARY Film Awards 2014]] for his directorial debut.<ref name="1st ARYFA">{{cite news|author=Saira Agha|title=‘Waar’ dominates ARY Film Awards with 13 major wins|url=http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/30-Apr-2014/waar-dominates-ary-film-awards-with-13-major-wins|accessdate=28 May 2014|newspaper=Daily Times|date=30 April 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141226094047/http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/30-Apr-2014/waar-dominates-ary-film-awards-with-13-major-wins|archivedate=26 December 2014|df=}}</ref>
== Early life & career == Lashari was born into a [[Baloch people|Baloch]] family. His father, Kamran Lashari, is a retired senior Pakistani bureaucrat who served as [[Petroleum Secretary of Pakistan]] and did a lot in cultural preservation, while his paternal grandfather was a landlord, lawyer and poet.<ref>[https://insidelahore.com/kamran-man-who-kept-culture-alive/ Kamran Lashari, The man who kept our Culture Alive]</ref> His younger brother, Rohail Lashari, has been the lead vocalist and rhythm guitarist for the [[Lahore]]-based band ''Jhol'' (2010-2015), was "in charge" of the seventh season of [[Coke Studio Pakistan]] as well as a [[MBA]] graduate from [[HEC Paris]], while another younger brother, Omar Lashari, is a [[Cornell]]-educated financial analyst.<ref>Rohail Lashari (18 January 2018), [https://blogs.tribune.com.pk/story/62639/i-wanted-to-earn-the-lashari-surname-and-studying-abroad-in-hec-paris-helped-me-achieve-just-that/ "I wanted to earn the ‘Lashari’ surname, and studying abroad in HEC Paris helped me achieve just that!"], ''[[The Express Tribune]]''. Retrieved 05 August 2018.</ref> Lashari grew up in Pakistan, attending local schools. He went to the [[United States of America]] for college, studying at the [[Academy of Art University]] in [[San Francisco, California]], where he earned a [[Bachelor of Fine Arts|Bachelor of Fine Arts (BFA)]] in Motion Pictures and Television in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://blogs.academyart.edu/newspaper/2015/12/9.html |title = Bringing Pakistan's Film Style to the World Stage - Academy of Art University |date =9 December 2015 |accessdate = 11 December 2016 |website = academyart.edu |publisher = [[Academy of Art University]]|last = |first = }}</ref>
After his return to Pakistan, Lashari first directed music videos, and won 'Best Music Video Director' twice at the [[Lux Style Awards]] and ‘Best Pop Video’ at the [[MTV Pakistan]] Music Video Awards for “Sajni”. He has also directed “Chal Bulleya” for Meekal Hassan Band. He has worked with artists and bands such as [[Abrarul Haq]], [[Atif Aslam]], Mekaal Hassan Band, [[Jal (band)|Jal]] and [[Entity Paradigm]]. He also directed the video “Chal Bulleya” for Meekal Hassan Band.
In 2004 Lashari briefly worked as assistant director for [[Shoaib Mansoor]] during pre-production of ''[[Khuda Kay Liye]]'' in 2004.
