The '''NHIF Civil Servants Scheme Scandal''' is an alleged scandal, relating to irregularities that were revealed in the [[Kenya]] Civil Servants Scheme at the [[National Hospital Insurance Fund]], in early 2012.<ref name="nation.co.ke">{{cite web|url=http://www.nation.co.ke/News/MPs-probe-finds-shocking-details-on-NHIF-scheme-/-/1056/1407216/-/d67iirz/-/index.html|title=MPs’ probe finds shocking details on NHIF scheme|website=Nation.co.ke|accessdate=19 October 2017}}</ref>
The alleged irregularities included payment to ghost clinics, unprocedural selection of clinics and creation of an unapproved unit at the NHIF.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nation.co.ke/News/Fresh-scandals-unearthed-in-health-scheme-/-/1056/1459554/-/v8fb4q/-/index.html|title=Fresh scandals unearthed in health scheme|website=Nation.co.ke|accessdate=19 October 2017}}</ref>
The scandal was subject to a probe by the Health Parliamentary Committee.<ref name="nation.co.ke"/> Most of the alleged claims were found to be incorrect with time by various enquiry commissions, however investigations are still going on.
