{{Infobox language |name=Rungtu |altname=Thaungtha |region=[[Burma]] |ethnicity= |speakers=5,000 |date=2015 |ref=<ref>[http://www-01.sil.org/iso639-3/chg_detail.asp?id=2011-016 ISO change request]</ref> |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Kuki-Chin languages|Kuki-Chin]] |fam4=[[Southern Kuki-Chin languages|Southern]] |iso3=rtc |glotto=none }}
'''Rungtu''' (Rungtu Chin) is a moribund [[Kuki-Chin languages|Kuki-Chin language]] of [[Burma]]. It is spoken in 35 villages in [[Htilin]], [[Kyaukhtu]], and [[Saw Township|Saw]] townships, [[Magway Region]].<ref>[https://www.ethnologue.com/language/rtc ''Ethnologue''] Nineteenth edition, 2016</ref> There are 3 dialects, namely Northern Rungtu, Central Rungtu, and Southern Rungtu.
